# WerkFlow Styling Guidelines

WerkFlow looks calm, professional, and deliberately understated. Clarity and trust beat visual excitement; the Aufträge and Dokumente tables are the reference for the intended feel.

**Source of truth:** all theme values live in `app/globals.css` (`:root` tokens + `@theme inline`). Change the look by editing tokens there; never hardcode hex values or one-off styles in components. The detailed design language lives in `.claude/skills/werkflow-design/SKILL.md` (mirrored in `.agents/skills/`).

## Color Roles

| Role                 | Token(s)                                        | Usage                                                                                     |
| -------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Orange (primary)** | `primary`, `--brand-orange` (`#ff7900`)         | The only attention color: submit/CTA buttons, focus rings, selection, important links      |
| **Purple (support)** | `--brand-purple*` scale, purple-tinted neutrals | Soft desaturated undertone; semantic hue for parked/planning entities (`geparkt`, Kalender) |
| **Neutrals**         | `background`, `card`, `muted`, `border`, …      | Most surfaces — they carry only a faint purple cast                                        |

- Orange must stay rare to keep its attention-grabbing role.
- Purple is deliberately desaturated (grayish). Do not reintroduce vivid violet (the old `#7b2cbf` family) in UI — only the logo SVGs keep vivid purple.
- Status colors stay semantic (green/red/yellow) — never rebrand them orange or purple.

## Pairing Rules (critical)

- ✅ Orange background + white/neutral text
- ✅ Purple background + white/neutral/purple text
- ✅ Neutral background + orange OR purple text
- ❌ Orange background + purple text
- ❌ Purple background + orange text
- Same rules apply in dark mode.

## Shape, Depth, Focus, Icons

- Modest radius (`--radius: 8px`): containers `rounded-lg`, controls `rounded-md`. Never `rounded-2xl`+; `rounded-full` only for avatars/dots/badges.
- Cards: `border` + `shadow-xs`. Heavy shadows only on floating elements (dialogs, popovers, toasts, drag previews).
- Focus: 2px orange ring (`focus-visible:ring-2`), no ring offsets, never 3px+ rings.
- Icons: Lucide with a global 1.75 stroke (set in `globals.css`) — do not pass `strokeWidth` props.
- Slim controls: tabs `h-9`, sidebar items `py-1.5`, active nav = quiet neutral fill, not a colored pill.
- Prefer sections with headings/dividers over wrapping every block in a card.

## Logo Usage

- Light mode: `/logo-text-light.svg` or `/logo-icon-light.svg`
- Dark mode: `/logo-text-dark.svg` or `/logo-icon-dark.svg`
- Swap with `dark:hidden` and `hidden dark:block`.
